# Student Clinic Visit Analysis

## Overview
This project analyzes student clinic visit records to identify patterns in healthcare usage among students. The analysis focuses on understanding the most common health issues, frequency of visits, and trends that may help improve student healthcare services.

## Objective
The objective of this project is to explore clinic visit data and generate insights that can help healthcare providers and school administrators better understand student health needs.

## Dataset
The dataset includes records of student visits to the campus clinic, containing information such as:
- Visit Date
- Student ID or Demographic Group
- Reason for Visit
- Diagnosis or Health Issue
- Treatment Provided
- Department or Unit Visited

## Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib / Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

## Analysis Performed
- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Frequency analysis of clinic visits
- Identification of the most common health complaints
- Trend analysis of visits over time
- Data visualization of clinic usage patterns

## Key Insights
- Identified the most common health issues affecting students
- Observed peak periods when clinic visits are highest
- Analyzed patterns that may indicate seasonal or environmental health trends

## Conclusion
The findings from this analysis can support better planning of healthcare resources in student clinics. By understanding visit patterns and common medical concerns, institutions can improve preventive health programs and ensure adequate medical support for students.
